verses.roman:
ei-mata paraspara paḍe huḍāhuḍi
paraspara bāḍhe, keha mukha nāhi muḍi

synonyms: ei mata—like this; paraspara—reciprocal; paḍe—happens; huḍāhuḍi—jostling; paraspara—mutually; bāḍhe—increases; keha—someone; mukha—face; nāhi—not; muḍi—covering.
translation: In this way a competition takes place between them in which no one acknowledges defeat.
